	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102761879380624><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=135&mid=102761879380624>Matches Dawnchaser</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=135&mid=102761879380624#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=8428><span id=Sage>Samsheed</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>53 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jul 25th 1:52 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.90]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Noticed that except for being 1Hb instead of Pierce, this thing matches the Dawnchaser.&nbsp;&nbsp;Assuming one didn't have a pair of better weapons for the 1HB and Pierce skills, this would make an interesting combo to meelee to keep those skills up.  And before anyone decides to flame that either of those weapon skills are &quot;useless&quot; for Bards, think about this:  <br><br>How would you feel if you flamed only to find out a couple of days later that some new Bard-usable 1HB (or Piercer, or whatever skill you said was &quot;useless&quot;) that was excellent had just been found?<br><br>Pardon me while I catch my breath from laughing at you frantically trying to improve a skill you thought was &quot;useless.&quot;  The point is- you NEVER KNOW what they may change on any given day.  Sure, there's gonna be one favorite skill you keep maxed b/c it's your best available weapon, but that's no reason not to keep the others up-to-spec as you go.  Get a decent group where you don't have to maintain the highest meelee output, and work on those &quot;secondary&quot; weapon skills.  Be prepared, and you'll fare better in the long run.<br>&nbsp;<br>Samsheed, 52 Human/MNK, Mahein 53 High Elf/ENC<br>&lt;Strength With Honor&gt;<br>Rodcet Nife</td></tr>
